---
title: Garlic Lime Chicken with Avocado Tomatillo Salsa
description: Tomatillos like to hide their charms. First, there’s the outer husks, which have to be peeled away in order to reveal the fruit. And even once you get to that fruit, it still looks a bit funny, like a green tomato gone awry. But once you cook tomatillos, they release all of their delicious, succulent juices, which mingle with creamy avocado, garlic-rubbed chicken, and sweet buttered corn in this recipe.
